          <h1>Vision 360⁰</h1>
          <h3>We are committed to making sure all of Northern California’s children can see well </h3>
          <p>
            See Well to Learn (SWTL) sets every preschooler up for success in school through early detection of vision problems.  Vision problems are one of the most prevalent disabling conditions among children, impacting their academic achievement trajectory.
            <br/>
            <br/>
            Despite extensive evidence that good vision is critical for early learning and development, parents of preschoolers living in high-poverty Northern California neighborhoods often find the barriers to care so overwhelming that children fail to receive the vision services they need.  This results in minority and low-income children being up to three times more likely to suffer from vision problems.
            <br/>
            <br/>
            To ensure that preschoolers in underserved communities have equal access to comprehensive vision care and are ready for school, Prevent Blindness Northern California (PBNC) and Tipping Point Community established SWTL in 2012 to provide Vision 360⁰ which includes not only advanced vision screening but also complete eye exams by licensed optometrists, prescription glasses, and support for parents and teachers — all for free and on school site.
          </p>
